-- 5. For drinkers who visits some bar less than 2 times a week, find the drinker’s name, the bar’s name and the bar’s address (in that order) [Output format: three columns named as ‘name’, ‘bar’, ‘address’ in this order]

SELECT frequents.drinker AS name,
       bar.name          AS bar,
       bar.address       AS address
FROM   frequents,
       bar
WHERE  bar.name = frequents.bar
       AND times_a_week < 2

SELECT DISTINCT frequents.drinker, bar.name, bar.address
FROM frequents, bar
WHERE frequents.times_a_week < 2 
AND frequents.bar = bar.name;

select frequents.drinker, bar.name, bar.address
from frequents, bar
where frequents.bar = bar.name
  and frequents.times_a_week < 2

Select F.drinker AS name, B.name AS bar, B.address
From frequents F, bar B
Where F.times_a_week < 2  AND F.bar = B.name
select f.drinker as name, b.name as bar, b.address from frequents f, bar b where f.times_a_week < 2 and f.bar = b.name

SELECT F.drinker AS name, F.bar, B.address
FROM frequents F, bar B
WHERE F.times_a_week < 2 AND F.bar = B.name
select frequents.drinker as name, frequents.bar, bar.address from frequents,bar where frequents.times_a_week<2 and frequents.bar=bar.name
select distinct A.drinker as name, B.name as bar, B.address from frequents A, bar B where A.times_a_week < 2 and A.bar = B.name
select f.drinker "name", f.bar, b.address from frequents f, bar b where f.bar=b.name and f.times_a_week < 2

SELECT F.drinker, F.bar, B.address
  FROM frequents F, bar B
  WHERE F.times_a_week < 2 AND B.name = F.bar

SELECT DISTINCT A.drinker as name, A.bar, B.address 
FROM Frequents A, Bar B 
WHERE times_a_week < 2 
AND A.bar = B.name

select frequents.drinker as name, frequents.bar, bar.address
from frequents, bar
where bar.name = frequents.bar
and frequents.times_a_week < 2

SELECT F.drinker AS name, F.bar, B.address
FROM bar B, frequents F
WHERE F.bar = B.name AND F.times_a_week < 2

select frequents.drinker as "name", bar.name as bar, bar.address as address
from frequents, bar
where bar.name = frequents.bar and frequents.times_a_week < 2
SELECT F.drinker, F.bar, B.address FROM Frequents F, Bar B WHERE F.bar = B.name AND F.times_a_week  < 2

SELECT drinker, bar, address
FROM frequents, bar 
WHERE times_a_week<2 and frequents.bar = bar.name

SELECT f.drinker AS name, f.bar AS bar, b.address AS address
FROM frequents f, bar b
WHERE f.times_a_week < 2 AND f.bar = b.name

SELECT DISTINCT f.drinker, f.bar, B.address
FROM frequents F, bar B
WHERE f.times_a_week < 2
AND f.bar = b.name

select F.drinker as name, B.name as bar, B.address as address
from frequents F, bar B
where F.times_a_week < 2 and F.bar = B.name

select D.name, B.name as bar, B.address
from drinker D, bar B, frequents F1, frequents F2
where F1.drinker = F2.drinker and F1.bar = F2.bar and F1.bar = B.name and F1.times_a_week <2 and F1.drinker = D.name

FROM bar B, frequents F
WHERE F.times_a_week < 2
AND F.bar = B.name

from drinker d, frequents f
where d.name = f.drinker

from bar b, frequents f

from frequents F, bar B
where F.times_a_week < 2 and F.bar = B.name

 FROM frequents f, bar b
 WHERE f.times_a_week < 2 AND f.bar = b.name

FROM frequents, bar
WHERE frequents.times_a_week < 2 AND frequents.bar = bar.name

--drinkers who visit some bar less than 2 times a week, find the drinker's name, bar's name, and the bar's address
select F.drinker as name, B.name bar, B.address
from frequents F, bar B
where F.times_a_week < 2
 and B.name = F.bar

FROM Frequents F, Bar B
